- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category, as the paper deals with parity games, which are a well-known topic in formal verification and logic. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely, as the paper proposes a new algorithm to solve parity games. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is another possible category, as parity games are a type of two-player game and the paper discusses attracting tangles, which are a concept from game theory. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category, as parity games have applications in automated reasoning and synthesis, which are topics in AI. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a less likely category, but still possible, as the paper proposes a new algorithm that could be implemented in programming languages.
